8 // ----
9 // This file contains a pass that expands pseudo instructions into target ----
10 // instructions. This pass should be run after register allocation but before ----
11 // the post-regalloc scheduling pass. ----
12 // ----
13 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----

39 } 0

109 ----
110 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expandMBB(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
111 bool Modified = false; 0
112 ----
113 BlockIt MBBI = MBB.begin(), E = MBB.end(); 0
114 while (MBBI != E) { 0
115 BlockIt NMBBI = std::next(MBBI); 0
116 Modified |= expandMI(MBB, MBBI); 0
117 MBBI = NMBBI; 0
118 } ----
119 ----
120 return Modified; 0
121 } ----
122 ----
123 bool AVRExpandPseudo::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
124 bool Modified = false; 0
125 ----
126 const AVRSubtarget &STI = MF.getSubtarget(); 0
127 TRI = STI.getRegisterInfo(); 0
128 TII = STI.getInstrInfo(); 0
129 ----
130 for (Block &MBB : MF) { 0
131 bool ContinueExpanding = true; 0
132 unsigned ExpandCount = 0; 0
133 ----
134 // Continue expanding the block until all pseudos are expanded. ----
135 do { 0
136 assert(ExpandCount < 10 && "pseudo expand limit reached"); 0
137 (void)ExpandCount; ----
138 ----
139 bool BlockModified = expandMBB(MBB); 0
140 Modified |= BlockModified; 0
141 ExpandCount++; 0
142 ----
143 ContinueExpanding = BlockModified; 0
144 } while (ContinueExpanding); ----
145 } ----
146 ----
147 return Modified; 0
148 } ----
149 ----
150 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expandArith(unsigned OpLo, unsigned OpHi, Block &MBB, 0
151 BlockIt MBBI) { ----
152 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
153 Register SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
154 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
155 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
156 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
157 bool DstIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
158 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(2).isKill(); 0
159 bool ImpIsDead = MI.getOperand(3).isDead(); 0
160 TRI->splitReg(SrcReg, SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg); 0
161 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0
162 ----
163 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpLo) 0
164 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
165 .addReg(DstLoReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)) 0
166 .addReg(SrcLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)); 0
167 ----
168 auto MIBHI = ----
169 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpHi) 0
170 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
171 .addReg(DstHiReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)) 0
172 .addReg(SrcHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)); 0
173 ----
174 if (ImpIsDead) 0
175 MIBHI->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); 0
176 ----
177 // SREG is always implicitly killed ----
178 MIBHI->getOperand(4).setIsKill(); 0
179 ----
180 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
181 return true; 0
182 } ----

218 bool AVRExpandPseudo::isLogicImmOpRedundant(unsigned Op, 0
219 unsigned ImmVal) const { ----
220 ----
221 // ANDI Rd, 0xff is redundant. ----
222 if (Op == AVR::ANDIRdK && ImmVal == 0xff) 0
223 return true; 0
224 ----
225 // ORI Rd, 0x0 is redundant. ----
226 if (Op == AVR::ORIRdK && ImmVal == 0x0) 0
227 return true; 0
228 ----
229 return false; 0
230 } ----
231 ----
232 bool AVRExpandPseudo::isLogicRegOpUndef(unsigned Op, unsigned ImmVal) const { 0
233 // ANDI Rd, 0x00 clears all input bits. ----
234 if (Op == AVR::ANDIRdK && ImmVal == 0x00) 0
235 return true; 0
236 ----
237 // ORI Rd, 0xff sets all input bits. ----
238 if (Op == AVR::ORIRdK && ImmVal == 0xff) 0
239 return true; 0
240 ----
241 return false; 0
242 } ----
243 ----
244 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expandLogicImm(unsigned Op, Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
245 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
246 Register DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
247 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
248 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
249 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
250 bool ImpIsDead = MI.getOperand(3).isDead(); 0
251 unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
252 unsigned Lo8 = Imm & 0xff; 0
253 unsigned Hi8 = (Imm >> 8) & 0xff; 0
254 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0
255 ----
256 if (!isLogicImmOpRedundant(Op, Lo8)) { 0
257 auto MIBLO = ----
258 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, Op) 0
259 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
260 .addReg(DstLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
261 .addImm(Lo8); 0
262 ----
263 // SREG is always implicitly dead ----
264 MIBLO->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); 0
265 ----
266 if (isLogicRegOpUndef(Op, Lo8)) 0
267 MIBLO->getOperand(1).setIsUndef(true); 0
268 } ----
269 ----
270 if (!isLogicImmOpRedundant(Op, Hi8)) { 0
271 auto MIBHI = ----
272 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, Op) 0
273 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
274 .addReg(DstHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
275 .addImm(Hi8); 0
276 ----
277 if (ImpIsDead) 0
278 MIBHI->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); 0
279 ----
280 if (isLogicRegOpUndef(Op, Hi8)) 0
281 MIBHI->getOperand(1).setIsUndef(true); 0
282 } ----
283 ----
284 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
285 return true; 0
286 } ----

304 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
305 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
306 Register DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
307 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
308 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
309 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
310 bool ImpIsDead = MI.getOperand(3).isDead(); 0
311 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0
312 ----
313 auto MIBLO = ----
314 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SUBIRdK) 0
315 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
316 .addReg(DstLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)); 0
317 ----
318 auto MIBHI = ----
319 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SBCIRdK) 0
320 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
321 .addReg(DstHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)); 0
322 ----
323 switch (MI.getOperand(2).getType()) { 0
324 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: { 0
325 const GlobalValue *GV = MI.getOperand(2).getGlobal(); 0
326 int64_t Offs = MI.getOperand(2).getOffset(); 0
327 unsigned TF = MI.getOperand(2).getTargetFlags(); 0
328 MIBLO.addGlobalAddress(GV, Offs, TF | AVRII::MO_NEG | AVRII::MO_LO); 0
329 MIBHI.addGlobalAddress(GV, Offs, TF | AVRII::MO_NEG | AVRII::MO_HI); 0
330 break; 0
331 } ----
332 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: { 0
333 unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
334 MIBLO.addImm(Imm & 0xff); 0
335 MIBHI.addImm((Imm >> 8) & 0xff); 0
336 break; 0
337 } ----
338 default: 0
339 llvm_unreachable("Unknown operand type!"); 0
340 } ----
341 ----
342 if (ImpIsDead) 0
343 MIBHI->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); 0
344 ----
345 // SREG is always implicitly killed ----
346 MIBHI->getOperand(4).setIsKill(); 0
347 ----
348 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
349 return true; 0
350 } ----

464 ----
465 // Do NEG on the upper byte. ----
466 auto MIBHI = ----
467 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::NEGRd) 0
468 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
469 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Kill); 0

471 MIBHI->getOperand(2).setIsDead(); 0
472 ----
473 // Do NEG on the lower byte. ----
474 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::NEGRd) 0
475 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
476 .addReg(DstLoReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)); 0

478 // Do an extra SBC. ----
479 auto MISBCI = ----
480 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SBCRdRr) 0
481 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
482 .addReg(DstHiReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)) 0
483 .addReg(ZeroReg); 0
484 if (ImpIsDead) 0
485 MISBCI->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); 0
486 // SREG is always implicitly killed ----
487 MISBCI->getOperand(4).setIsKill(); 0
488 ----
489 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
490 return true; 0
491 } ----

577 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
578 ----
579 switch (MI.getOperand(1).getType()) { 0
580 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: { 0
581 const GlobalValue *GV = MI.getOperand(1).getGlobal(); 0
582 int64_t Offs = MI.getOperand(1).getOffset(); 0
583 unsigned TF = MI.getOperand(1).getTargetFlags(); 0
584 ----
585 MIBLO.addGlobalAddress(GV, Offs, TF | AVRII::MO_LO); 0
586 MIBHI.addGlobalAddress(GV, Offs, TF | AVRII::MO_HI); 0
587 break; 0
588 } ----
589 case MachineOperand::MO_BlockAddress: { 0
590 const BlockAddress *BA = MI.getOperand(1).getBlockAddress(); 0
591 unsigned TF = MI.getOperand(1).getTargetFlags(); 0
592 ----
593 MIBLO.add(MachineOperand::CreateBA(BA, TF | AVRII::MO_LO)); 0
594 MIBHI.add(MachineOperand::CreateBA(BA, TF | AVRII::MO_HI)); 0
595 break; 0
596 } ----
597 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: { 0
598 unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
599 ----
600 MIBLO.addImm(Imm & 0xff); 0
601 MIBHI.addImm((Imm >> 8) & 0xff); 0
602 break; 0
603 } ----
604 default: 0
605 llvm_unreachable("Unknown operand type!"); 0
606 } ----
607 ----
608 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
609 return true; 0
610 } ----
611 ----
612 template <> ----
613 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
614 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
615 Register DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
616 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
617 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
618 unsigned OpLo = AVR::LDSRdK; 0
619 unsigned OpHi = AVR::LDSRdK; 0
620 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0
621 ----
622 auto MIBLO = ----
623 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpLo) 0
624 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
625 ----
626 auto MIBHI = ----
627 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpHi) 0
628 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
629 ----
630 switch (MI.getOperand(1).getType()) { 0
631 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: { 0
632 const GlobalValue *GV = MI.getOperand(1).getGlobal(); 0
633 int64_t Offs = MI.getOperand(1).getOffset(); 0
634 unsigned TF = MI.getOperand(1).getTargetFlags(); 0
635 ----
636 MIBLO.addGlobalAddress(GV, Offs, TF); 0
637 MIBHI.addGlobalAddress(GV, Offs + 1, TF); 0
638 break; 0
639 } ----
640 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: { 0
641 unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
642 ----
643 MIBLO.addImm(Imm); 0
644 MIBHI.addImm(Imm + 1); 0
645 break; 0
646 } ----
647 default: 0
648 llvm_unreachable("Unknown operand type!"); 0
649 } ----
650 ----
651 MIBLO.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
652 MIBHI.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
653 ----
654 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
655 return true; 0
656 } ----

658 template <> ----
659 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
660 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
661 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
662 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
663 bool DstIsKill = MI.getOperand(0).isKill(); 0
664 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
665 const AVRSubtarget &STI = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget(); 0
666 ----
667 // DstReg has an earlyclobber so the register allocator will allocate them in ----
668 // separate registers. ----
669 assert(DstReg != SrcReg && "Dst and Src registers are the same!"); 0
670 ----
671 if (STI.hasTinyEncoding()) { 0
672 // Handle this case in the expansion of LDDWRdPtrQ because it is very ----
673 // similar. ----
674 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::LDDWRdPtrQ) 0
675 .addDef(DstReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)) 0
676 .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
677 .addImm(0) 0
678 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
679 ----
680 } else { ----
681 Register DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
682 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0
683 ----
684 // Load low byte. ----
685 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::LDRdPtr) 0
686 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define) 0
687 .addReg(SrcReg) 0
688 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
689 ----
690 // Load high byte. ----
691 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::LDDRdPtrQ) 0
692 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define) 0
693 .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
694 .addImm(1) 0
695 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
696 } ----
697 ----
698 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
699 return true; 0
700 } ----

702 template <> ----
703 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
704 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
705 Register DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
706 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
707 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
708 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
709 bool SrcIsDead = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
710 unsigned OpLo = AVR::LDRdPtrPi; 0
711 unsigned OpHi = AVR::LDRdPtrPi; 0
712 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0
713 ----
714 assert(DstReg != SrcReg && "SrcReg and DstReg cannot be the same"); 0
715 ----
716 auto MIBLO = ----
717 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpLo) 0
718 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
719 .addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Define) 0
720 .addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Kill); 0

723 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpHi) 0
724 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
725 .addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(SrcIsDead)) 0
726 .addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Kill); 0
727 ----
728 MIBLO.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
729 MIBHI.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
730 ----
731 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
732 return true; 0

735 template <> ----
736 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
737 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
738 Register DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
739 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
740 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
741 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
742 bool SrcIsDead = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
743 unsigned OpLo = AVR::LDRdPtrPd; 0
744 unsigned OpHi = AVR::LDRdPtrPd; 0
745 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0
746 ----
747 assert(DstReg != SrcReg && "SrcReg and DstReg cannot be the same"); 0
748 ----
749 auto MIBHI = ----
750 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpHi) 0
751 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
752 .addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Define) 0
753 .addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Kill); 0
754 ----
755 auto MIBLO = ----
756 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpLo) 0
757 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
758 .addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(SrcIsDead)) 0
759 .addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Kill); 0
760 ----
761 MIBLO.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
762 MIBHI.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
763 ----
764 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
765 return true; 0
766 } ----
767 ----
768 template <> ----
769 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
770 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
771 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
772 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
773 unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
774 bool DstIsKill = MI.getOperand(0).isKill(); 0
775 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
776 const AVRSubtarget &STI = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget(); 0
777 ----
778 // Since we add 1 to the Imm value for the high byte below, and 63 is the ----
779 // highest Imm value allowed for the instruction, 62 is the limit here. ----
780 assert(Imm <= 62 && "Offset is out of range"); 0
781 ----
782 // DstReg has an earlyclobber so the register allocator will allocate them in ----
783 // separate registers. ----
784 assert(DstReg != SrcReg && "Dst and Src registers are the same!"); 0
785 ----
786 if (STI.hasTinyEncoding()) { 0
787 // Reduced tiny cores don't support load/store with displacement. However, ----
788 // they do support postincrement. So we'll simply adjust the pointer before ----
789 // and after and use postincrement to load multiple registers. ----
790 ----
791 // Add offset. The offset can be 0 when expanding this instruction from the ----
792 // more specific LDWRdPtr instruction. ----
793 if (Imm != 0) { 0
794 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SUBIWRdK, SrcReg) 0
795 .addReg(SrcReg) 0
796 .addImm(0x10000 - Imm); 0
797 } ----
798 ----
799 // Do a word load with postincrement. This will be lowered to a two byte ----
800 // load. ----
801 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::LDWRdPtrPi) 0
802 .addDef(DstReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)) 0
803 .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
804 .addImm(0) 0
805 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
806 ----
807 // If the pointer is used after the store instruction, subtract the new ----
808 // offset (with 2 added after the postincrement instructions) so it is the ----
809 // same as before. ----
810 if (!SrcIsKill) { 0
811 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SUBIWRdK, SrcReg).addReg(SrcReg).addImm(Imm + 2); 0
812 } ----
813 } else { ----
814 Register DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
815 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0
816 ----
817 // Load low byte. ----
818 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::LDDRdPtrQ) 0
819 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define) 0
820 .addReg(SrcReg) 0
821 .addImm(Imm) 0
822 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
823 ----
824 // Load high byte. ----
825 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::LDDRdPtrQ) 0
826 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define) 0
827 .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
828 .addImm(Imm + 1) 0
829 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
830 } ----
831 ----
832 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
833 return true; 0
834 } ----
835 ----
836 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expandLPMWELPMW(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI, bool IsELPM) { 0
837 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
838 Register DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
839 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
840 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
841 Register SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg; 0
842 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
843 const AVRSubtarget &STI = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget(); 0
844 bool IsLPMRn = IsELPM ? STI.hasELPMX() : STI.hasLPMX(); 0
845 ----
846 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0
847 TRI->splitReg(SrcReg, SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg); 0
848 ----
849 // Set the I/O register RAMPZ for ELPM. ----
850 if (IsELPM) { 0
851 Register Bank = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
852 // out RAMPZ, rtmp ----
853 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::OUTARr).addImm(STI.getIORegRAMPZ()).addReg(Bank); 0
854 } ----
855 ----
856 // This is enforced by the @earlyclobber constraint. ----
857 assert(DstReg != SrcReg && "SrcReg and DstReg cannot be the same"); 0
858 ----
859 if (IsLPMRn) { 0
860 unsigned OpLo = IsELPM ? AVR::ELPMRdZPi : AVR::LPMRdZPi; 0
861 unsigned OpHi = IsELPM ? AVR::ELPMRdZ : AVR::LPMRdZ; 0
862 // Load low byte. ----
863 auto MIBLO = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpLo) 0
864 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define) 0
865 .addReg(SrcReg); 0
866 // Load high byte. ----
867 auto MIBHI = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpHi) 0
868 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define) 0
869 .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)); 0
870 MIBLO.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
871 MIBHI.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
872 } else { ----
873 unsigned Opc = IsELPM ? AVR::ELPM : AVR::LPM; 0
874 // Load low byte, and copy to the low destination register. ----
875 auto MIBLO = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, Opc); 0
876 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::MOVRdRr) 0
877 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define) 0
878 .addReg(AVR::R0, RegState::Kill); 0
879 MIBLO.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
880 // Increase the Z register by 1. ----
881 if (STI.hasADDSUBIW()) { 0
882 // adiw r31:r30, 1 ----
883 auto MIINC = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::ADIWRdK) 0
884 .addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Define) 0
885 .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
886 .addImm(1); 0
887 MIINC->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); 0
888 } else { ----
889 // subi r30, 255 ----
890 // sbci r31, 255 ----
891 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SUBIRdK) 0
892 .addReg(SrcLoReg, RegState::Define) 0
893 .addReg(SrcLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
894 .addImm(255); 0
895 auto MIZHI = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SBCIRdK) 0
896 .addReg(SrcHiReg, RegState::Define) 0
897 .addReg(SrcHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
898 .addImm(255); 0
899 MIZHI->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); 0
900 MIZHI->getOperand(4).setIsKill(); 0
901 } ----
902 // Load high byte, and copy to the high destination register. ----
903 auto MIBHI = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, Opc); 0
904 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::MOVRdRr) 0
905 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define) 0
906 .addReg(AVR::R0, RegState::Kill); 0
907 MIBHI.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
908 } ----
909 ----
910 // Restore the Z register if it is not killed. ----
911 if (!SrcIsKill) { 0
912 if (STI.hasADDSUBIW()) { 0
913 // sbiw r31:r30, 1 ----
914 auto MIDEC = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SBIWRdK) 0
915 .addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Define) 0
916 .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
917 .addImm(1); 0
918 MIDEC->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); 0
919 } else { ----
920 // subi r30, 1 ----
921 // sbci r31, 0 ----
922 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SUBIRdK) 0
923 .addReg(SrcLoReg, RegState::Define) 0
924 .addReg(SrcLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
925 .addImm(1); 0
926 auto MIZHI = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SBCIRdK) 0
927 .addReg(SrcHiReg, RegState::Define) 0
928 .addReg(SrcHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
929 .addImm(0); 0
930 MIZHI->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); 0
931 MIZHI->getOperand(4).setIsKill(); 0
932 } ----
933 } ----
934 ----
935 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
936 return true; 0
937 } ----
938 ----
939 template <> ----
940 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
941 return expandLPMWELPMW(MBB, MBBI, false); 0
942 } ----
943 ----
944 template <> ----
945 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
946 return expandLPMWELPMW(MBB, MBBI, true); 0
947 } ----
948 ----
949 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expandLPMBELPMB(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI, bool IsELPM) { 0
950 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
951 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
952 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
953 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
954 const AVRSubtarget &STI = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget(); 0
955 bool IsLPMRn = IsELPM ? STI.hasELPMX() : STI.hasLPMX(); 0
956 ----
957 // Set the I/O register RAMPZ for ELPM (out RAMPZ, rtmp). ----
958 if (IsELPM) { 0
959 Register BankReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
960 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::OUTARr).addImm(STI.getIORegRAMPZ()).addReg(BankReg); 0
961 } ----
962 ----
963 // Load byte. ----
964 if (IsLPMRn) { 0
965 unsigned Opc = IsELPM ? AVR::ELPMRdZ : AVR::LPMRdZ; 0
966 auto MILB = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, Opc) 0
967 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define) 0
968 .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)); 0
969 MILB.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
970 } else { ----
971 // For the basic ELPM/LPM instruction, its operand[0] is the implicit ----
972 // 'Z' register, and its operand[1] is the implicit 'R0' register. ----
973 unsigned Opc = IsELPM ? AVR::ELPM : AVR::LPM; 0
974 auto MILB = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, Opc); 0
975 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::MOVRdRr) 0
976 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define) 0
977 .addReg(AVR::R0, RegState::Kill); 0
978 MILB.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
979 } ----
980 ----
981 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
982 return true; 0
983 } ----

1011 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expandAtomic(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI, Func f) { 0
1012 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1013 const AVRSubtarget &STI = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget(); 0
1014 ----
1015 // Store the SREG. ----
1016 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::INRdA) 0
1017 .addReg(STI.getTmpRegister(), RegState::Define) 0
1018 .addImm(STI.getIORegSREG()); 0
1019 ----
1020 // Disable exceptions. ----
1021 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::BCLRs).addImm(7); // CLI 0
1022 ----
1023 f(MI); 0
1024 ----
1025 // Restore the status reg. ----
1026 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::OUTARr) 0
1027 .addImm(STI.getIORegSREG()) 0
1028 .addReg(STI.getTmpRegister()); 0
1029 ----
1030 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1031 return true; 0
1032 } ----

1039 auto Op2 = MI.getOperand(1); 0
1040 ----
1041 MachineInstr &NewInst = ----
1042 *buildMI(MBB, MBBI, Opcode).add(Op1).add(Op2).getInstr(); 0
1043 f(NewInst); 0
1044 }); 0
1045 } ----

1072 template <> ----
1073 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1074 // On AVR, there is only one core and so atomic fences do nothing. ----
1075 MBBI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1076 return true; 0

1078 ----
1079 template <> ----
1080 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1081 const AVRSubtarget &STI = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget(); 0
1082 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1083 Register SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg; 0
1084 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1085 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
1086 TRI->splitReg(SrcReg, SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg); 0
1087 ----
1088 auto MIB0 = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::STSKRr); 0
1089 auto MIB1 = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::STSKRr); 0
1090 ----
1091 switch (MI.getOperand(0).getType()) { 0
1092 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: { 0
1093 const GlobalValue *GV = MI.getOperand(0).getGlobal(); 0
1094 int64_t Offs = MI.getOperand(0).getOffset(); 0
1095 unsigned TF = MI.getOperand(0).getTargetFlags(); 0
1096 ----
1097 if (STI.hasLowByteFirst()) { 0
1098 // Write the low byte first for XMEGA devices. ----
1099 MIB0.addGlobalAddress(GV, Offs, TF); 0
1100 MIB1.addGlobalAddress(GV, Offs + 1, TF); 0
1101 } else { ----
1102 // Write the high byte first for traditional devices. ----
1103 MIB0.addGlobalAddress(GV, Offs + 1, TF); 0
1104 MIB1.addGlobalAddress(GV, Offs, TF); 0
1105 } ----
1106 ----
1107 break; 0
1108 } ----
1109 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: { 0
1110 unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(0).getImm(); 0
1111 ----
1112 if (STI.hasLowByteFirst()) { 0
1113 // Write the low byte first for XMEGA devices. ----
1114 MIB0.addImm(Imm); 0
1115 MIB1.addImm(Imm + 1); 0
1116 } else { ----
1117 // Write the high byte first for traditional devices. ----
1118 MIB0.addImm(Imm + 1); 0
1119 MIB1.addImm(Imm); 0
1120 } ----
1121 ----
1122 break; 0
1123 } ----
1124 default: 0
1125 llvm_unreachable("Unknown operand type!"); 0
1126 } ----
1127 ----
1128 if (STI.hasLowByteFirst()) { 0
1129 // Write the low byte first for XMEGA devices. ----
1130 MIB0.addReg(SrcLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1131 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1132 MIB1.addReg(SrcHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1133 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1134 } else { ----
1135 // Write the high byte first for traditional devices. ----
1136 MIB0.addReg(SrcHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1137 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1138 MIB1.addReg(SrcLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1139 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1140 } ----
1141 ----
1142 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1143 return true; 0
1144 } ----
1145 ----
1146 template <> ----
1147 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1148 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1149 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1150 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1151 bool DstIsKill = MI.getOperand(0).isKill(); 0
1152 bool DstIsUndef = MI.getOperand(0).isUndef(); 0
1153 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
1154 const AVRSubtarget &STI = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget(); 0
1155 ----
1156 //: TODO: need to reverse this order like inw and stsw? ----
1157 ----
1158 if (STI.hasTinyEncoding()) { 0
1159 // Handle this case in the expansion of STDWPtrQRr because it is very ----
1160 // similar. ----
1161 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::STDWPtrQRr) 0
1162 .addReg(DstReg, 0
1163 getKillRegState(DstIsKill) | getUndefRegState(DstIsUndef)) 0
1164 .addImm(0) 0
1165 .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1166 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1167 ----
1168 } else { ----
1169 Register SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg; 0
1170 TRI->splitReg(SrcReg, SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg); 0
1171 if (STI.hasLowByteFirst()) { 0
1172 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::STPtrRr) 0
1173 .addReg(DstReg, getUndefRegState(DstIsUndef)) 0
1174 .addReg(SrcLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1175 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1176 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::STDPtrQRr) 0
1177 .addReg(DstReg, getUndefRegState(DstIsUndef)) 0
1178 .addImm(1) 0
1179 .addReg(SrcHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1180 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1181 } else { ----
1182 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::STDPtrQRr) 0
1183 .addReg(DstReg, getUndefRegState(DstIsUndef)) 0
1184 .addImm(1) 0
1185 .addReg(SrcHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1186 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1187 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::STPtrRr) 0
1188 .addReg(DstReg, getUndefRegState(DstIsUndef)) 0
1189 .addReg(SrcLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1190 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1191 } ----
1192 } ----
1193 ----
1194 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1195 return true; 0
1196 } ----

1199 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1200 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1201 Register SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg; 0
1202 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1203 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1204 unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
1205 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
1206 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(2).isKill(); 0
1207 unsigned OpLo = AVR::STPtrPiRr; 0
1208 unsigned OpHi = AVR::STPtrPiRr; 0
1209 TRI->splitReg(SrcReg, SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg); 0
1210 ----
1211 assert(DstReg != SrcReg && "SrcReg and DstReg cannot be the same"); 0
1212 ----
1213 auto MIBLO = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpLo) 0
1214 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define) 0
1215 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Kill) 0
1216 .addReg(SrcLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1217 .addImm(Imm); 0
1218 ----
1219 auto MIBHI = ----
1220 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpHi) 0
1221 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1222 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Kill) 0
1223 .addReg(SrcHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1224 .addImm(Imm); 0
1225 ----
1226 MIBLO.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1227 MIBHI.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1228 ----
1229 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1230 return true; 0
1231 } ----

1237 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1238 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0

1242 unsigned OpLo = AVR::STPtrPdRr; 0
1243 unsigned OpHi = AVR::STPtrPdRr; 0

1245 ----
1246 assert(DstReg != SrcReg && "SrcReg and DstReg cannot be the same"); 0
1247 ----

1249 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define) 0

1251 .addReg(SrcHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1252 .addImm(Imm); 0

1256 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1257 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Kill) 0
1258 .addReg(SrcLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0

1267 ----
1268 template <> ----
1269 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1270 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1271 const AVRSubtarget &STI = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget(); 0
1272 ----
1273 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1274 bool DstIsKill = MI.getOperand(0).isKill(); 0
1275 unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
1276 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1277 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(2).isKill(); 0
1278 ----
1279 // STD's maximum displacement is 63, so larger stores have to be split into a ----
1280 // set of operations. ----
1281 // For avrtiny chips, STD is not available at all so we always have to fall ----
1282 // back to manual pointer adjustments. ----
1283 if (Imm >= 63 || STI.hasTinyEncoding()) { 0
1284 // Add offset. The offset can be 0 when expanding this instruction from the ----
1285 // more specific STWPtrRr instruction. ----
1286 if (Imm != 0) { 0
1287 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SUBIWRdK, DstReg) 0
1288 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Kill) 0
1289 .addImm(0x10000 - Imm); 0
1290 } ----
1291 ----
1292 // Do the store. This is a word store, that will be expanded further. ----
1293 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::STWPtrPiRr, DstReg) 0
1294 .addReg(DstReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)) 0
1295 .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1296 .addImm(0) 0
1297 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1298 ----
1299 // If the pointer is used after the store instruction, subtract the new ----
1300 // offset (with 2 added after the postincrement instructions) so it is the ----
1301 // same as before. ----
1302 if (!DstIsKill) { 0
1303 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SUBIWRdK, DstReg) 0
1304 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Kill) 0
1305 .addImm(Imm + 2); 0
1306 } ----
1307 } else { ----
1308 Register SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg; 0
1309 TRI->splitReg(SrcReg, SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg); 0
1310 ----
1311 if (STI.hasLowByteFirst()) { 0
1312 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::STDPtrQRr) 0
1313 .addReg(DstReg) 0
1314 .addImm(Imm) 0
1315 .addReg(SrcLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1316 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1317 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::STDPtrQRr) 0
1318 .addReg(DstReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)) 0
1319 .addImm(Imm + 1) 0
1320 .addReg(SrcHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1321 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1322 } else { ----
1323 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::STDPtrQRr) 0
1324 .addReg(DstReg) 0
1325 .addImm(Imm + 1) 0
1326 .addReg(SrcHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1327 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1328 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::STDPtrQRr) 0
1329 .addReg(DstReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)) 0
1330 .addImm(Imm) 0
1331 .addReg(SrcLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1332 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1333 } ----
1334 } ----
1335 ----
1336 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1337 return true; 0
1338 } ----
1339 ----
1340 template <> ----
1341 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1342 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1343 const MachineFunction &MF = *MBB.getParent(); 0
1344 const AVRSubtarget &STI = MF.getSubtarget(); 0
1345 ----
1346 assert(MI.getOperand(0).getReg() == AVR::SP && 0
1347 "SP is expected as base pointer"); ----
1348 ----
1349 assert(STI.getFrameLowering()->hasReservedCallFrame(MF) && 0
1350 "unexpected STDSPQRr pseudo instruction"); ----
1351 (void)STI; ----
1352 ----
1353 MI.setDesc(TII->get(AVR::STDPtrQRr)); 0
1354 MI.getOperand(0).setReg(AVR::R29R28); 0
1355 ----
1356 return true; 0
1357 } ----

1378 template <> ----
1379 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1380 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1381 Register DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
1382 unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
1383 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1384 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
1385 unsigned OpLo = AVR::INRdA; 0
1386 unsigned OpHi = AVR::INRdA; 0
1387 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0
1388 ----
1389 // Since we add 1 to the Imm value for the high byte below, and 63 is the ----
1390 // highest Imm value allowed for the instruction, 62 is the limit here. ----
1391 assert(Imm <= 62 && "Address is out of range"); 0
1392 ----
1393 auto MIBLO = ----
1394 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpLo) 0
1395 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1396 .addImm(Imm); 0
1397 ----
1398 auto MIBHI = ----
1399 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpHi) 0
1400 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1401 .addImm(Imm + 1); 0
1402 ----
1403 MIBLO.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1404 MIBHI.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1405 ----
1406 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1407 return true; 0

1410 template <> ----
1411 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1412 const AVRSubtarget &STI = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget(); 0
1413 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1414 Register SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg; 0
1415 unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(0).getImm(); 0
1416 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1417 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
1418 TRI->splitReg(SrcReg, SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg); 0
1419 ----
1420 // Since we add 1 to the Imm value for the high byte below, and 63 is the ----
1421 // highest Imm value allowed for the instruction, 62 is the limit here. ----
1422 assert(Imm <= 62 && "Address is out of range"); 0
1423 ----
1424 // 16 bit I/O writes need the high byte first on normal AVR devices, ----
1425 // and in reverse order for the XMEGA/XMEGA3/XMEGAU families. ----
1426 auto MIBHI = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::OUTARr) 0
1427 .addImm(STI.hasLowByteFirst() ? Imm : Imm + 1) 0
1428 .addReg(STI.hasLowByteFirst() ? SrcLoReg : SrcHiReg, 0
1429 getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)); 0
1430 auto MIBLO = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::OUTARr) 0
1431 .addImm(STI.hasLowByteFirst() ? Imm + 1 : Imm) 0
1432 .addReg(STI.hasLowByteFirst() ? SrcHiReg : SrcLoReg, 0
1433 getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)); 0
1434 ----
1435 MIBLO.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1436 MIBHI.setMemRefs(MI.memoperands()); 0
1437 ----
1438 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1439 return true; 0
1440 } ----

1443 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1444 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1445 Register SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg; 0
1446 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1447 bool SrcIsKill = MI.getOperand(0).isKill(); 0
1448 unsigned Flags = MI.getFlags(); 0
1449 unsigned OpLo = AVR::PUSHRr; 0
1450 unsigned OpHi = AVR::PUSHRr; 0
1451 TRI->splitReg(SrcReg, SrcLoReg, SrcHiReg); 0
1452 ----
1453 // Low part ----
1454 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpLo) 0
1455 .addReg(SrcLoReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1456 .setMIFlags(Flags); 0
1457 ----
1458 // High part ----
1459 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpHi) 0
1460 .addReg(SrcHiReg, getKillRegState(SrcIsKill)) 0
1461 .setMIFlags(Flags); 0
1462 ----
1463 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1464 return true; 0

1468 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1469 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1470 Register DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
1471 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1472 unsigned Flags = MI.getFlags(); 0
1473 unsigned OpLo = AVR::POPRd; 0
1474 unsigned OpHi = AVR::POPRd; 0
1475 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0
1476 ----
1477 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpHi, DstHiReg).setMIFlags(Flags); // High 0
1478 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpLo, DstLoReg).setMIFlags(Flags); // Low 0
1479 ----
1480 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1481 return true; 0

1483 ----
1484 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expandROLBRd(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1485 // In AVR, the rotate instructions behave quite unintuitively. They rotate ----
1486 // bits through the carry bit in SREG, effectively rotating over 9 bits, ----
1487 // instead of 8. This is useful when we are dealing with numbers over ----
1488 // multiple registers, but when we actually need to rotate stuff, we have ----
1489 // to explicitly add the carry bit. ----
1490 ----
1491 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1492 unsigned OpShift, OpCarry; ----
1493 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1494 Register ZeroReg = MI.getOperand(3).getReg(); 0
1495 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
1496 bool DstIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
1497 OpShift = AVR::ADDRdRr; 0
1498 OpCarry = AVR::ADCRdRr; 0
1499 ----
1500 // add r16, r16 ----
1501 // adc r16, r1 ----
1502 ----
1503 // Shift part ----
1504 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpShift) 0
1505 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1506 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Kill) 0
1507 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Kill); 0
1508 ----
1509 // Add the carry bit ----
1510 auto MIB = buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpCarry) 0
1511 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1512 .addReg(DstReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)) 0
1513 .addReg(ZeroReg); 0
1514 ----
1515 MIB->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); // SREG is always dead 0
1516 MIB->getOperand(4).setIsKill(); // SREG is always implicitly killed 0
1517 ----
1518 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1519 return true; 0
1520 } ----
1521 ----
1522 template <> ----
1523 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1524 return expandROLBRd(MBB, MBBI); 0
1525 } ----
1526 ----
1527 template <> ----
1528 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1529 return expandROLBRd(MBB, MBBI); 0
1530 } ----

1532 template <> ----
1533 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1534 // In AVR, the rotate instructions behave quite unintuitively. They rotate ----
1535 // bits through the carry bit in SREG, effectively rotating over 9 bits, ----
1536 // instead of 8. This is useful when we are dealing with numbers over ----
1537 // multiple registers, but when we actually need to rotate stuff, we have ----
1538 // to explicitly add the carry bit. ----
1539 ----
1540 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1541 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1542 ----
1543 // bst r16, 0 ----
1544 // ror r16 ----
1545 // bld r16, 7 ----
1546 ----
1547 // Move the lowest bit from DstReg into the T bit ----
1548 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::BST).addReg(DstReg).addImm(0); 0
1549 ----
1550 // Rotate to the right ----
1551 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::RORRd, DstReg).addReg(DstReg); 0
1552 ----
1553 // Move the T bit into the highest bit of DstReg. ----
1554 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::BLD, DstReg).addReg(DstReg).addImm(7); 0
1555 ----
1556 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1557 return true; 0
1558 } ----
1559 ----
1560 template <> ----
1561 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expand(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1562 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1563 Register DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
1564 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1565 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
1566 bool DstIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
1567 bool ImpIsDead = MI.getOperand(2).isDead(); 0
1568 unsigned OpLo = AVR::ADDRdRr; // ADD Rd, Rd <==> LSL Rd 0
1569 unsigned OpHi = AVR::ADCRdRr; // ADC Rd, Rd <==> ROL Rd 0
1570 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0
1571 ----
1572 // Low part ----
1573 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpLo) 0
1574 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1575 .addReg(DstLoReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)) 0
1576 .addReg(DstLoReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)); 0
1577 ----
1578 auto MIBHI = ----
1579 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, OpHi) 0
1580 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1581 .addReg(DstHiReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)) 0
1582 .addReg(DstHiReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)); 0
1583 ----
1584 if (ImpIsDead) 0
1585 MIBHI->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); 0
1586 ----
1587 // SREG is always implicitly killed ----
1588 MIBHI->getOperand(4).setIsKill(); 0
1589 ----
1590 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1591 return true; 0
1592 } ----

1597 Register DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
1598 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1599 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
1600 bool DstIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
1601 bool ImpIsDead = MI.getOperand(2).isDead(); 0
1602 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0

1609 .addReg(DstHiReg, getKillRegState(DstIsKill)); 0

1611 if (ImpIsDead) 0
1612 MILSL->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); 0

1617 ----
1618 bool AVRExpandPseudo::expandLSLW4Rd(Block &MBB, BlockIt MBBI) { 0
1619 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1620 Register DstLoReg, DstHiReg; 0
1621 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1622 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
1623 bool DstIsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill(); 0
1624 bool ImpIsDead = MI.getOperand(3).isDead(); 0
1625 TRI->splitReg(DstReg, DstLoReg, DstHiReg); 0
1626 ----
1627 // swap Rh ----
1628 // swap Rl ----
1629 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SWAPRd) 0
1630 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1631 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Kill); 0
1632 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::SWAPRd) 0
1633 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1634 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Kill); 0
1635 ----
1636 // andi Rh, 0xf0 ----
1637 auto MI0 = ----
1638 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::ANDIRdK) 0
1639 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1640 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Kill) 0
1641 .addImm(0xf0); 0
1642 // SREG is implicitly dead. ----
1643 MI0->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); 0
1644 ----
1645 // eor Rh, Rl ----
1646 auto MI1 = ----
1647 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::EORRdRr) 0
1648 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0
1649 .addReg(DstHiReg, RegState::Kill) 0
1650 .addReg(DstLoReg); 0
1651 // SREG is implicitly dead. ----
1652 MI1->getOperand(3).setIsDead(); 0
1653 ----
1654 // andi Rl, 0xf0 ----
1655 auto MI2 = ----
1656 buildMI(MBB, MBBI, AVR::ANDIRdK) 0
1657 .addReg(DstLoReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)) 0

218 bool AVRExpandPseudo::isLogicImmOpRedundant(unsigned Op, 218 bool AVRExpandPseudo::isLogicImmOpRedundant(unsigned Op,
219 unsigned ImmVal) const { 219 unsigned ImmVal) const {
220 220
221 // ANDI Rd, 0xff is redundant. 221 // ANDI Rd, 0xff is redundant.
222 if (Op == AVR::ANDIRdK && ImmVal == 0xff) 222 if (Op == AVR::ANDIRdK && ImmVal == 0xff)
223 return true; 223 return true;
224 224
225 // ORI Rd, 0x0 is redundant. 225 // ORI Rd, 0x0 is redundant.
226 if (Op == AVR::ORIRdK && ImmVal == 0x0) 226 if (Op == AVR::ORIRdK && ImmVal == 0x0)
227 return true; 227 return true;
228 228
229 return false; 229 return false;
230 } 230 }

234 if (Op == AVR::ANDIRdK && ImmVal == 0x00) 234 if (Op == AVR::ANDIRdK && ImmVal == 0x00)

236 236

238 if (Op == AVR::ORIRdK && ImmVal == 0xff) 238 if (Op == AVR::ORIRdK && ImmVal == 0xff)
239 return true; 239 return true;
240 240
241 return false; 241 return false;
242 } 242 }
